title.narrative: HEALTH PROMOTION

description.narrative: Male and female caregivers and family and community members, especially the most disadvantaged in selected provinces, have improved knowledge and understanding regarding timely care-seeking and caring practices for quality immunization and MNCAH services, including the prevention of parent-to-child transmission of HIV and AIDS for their children., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Communities, parents, caregivers and children have increased awareness of the consequences of violence and have the skills to protect children and women.

description.narrative: UNICEF provided Immunization IEC materials and training of HW on ACSM in 3 provinces through Immunization in Practice. Two CSO have been engaged by UNICEF to engage communities with messages for continuation of immunisation. Despite COVID-19 pandemic, Penta-3 coverage reached to 34%. Community-based newborn care programme supported 109 pregnant women to access ANC and 86 supervised hospital deliveries were conducted and 78 village births were supported by VHVs respectively. Village health volunteers (VHVs) conducted 287 community meetings attended by 18,527 participants to promote the importance timely care-seeking practices, maternal health information including on nutrition, hygiene and family planning advice. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/12/2021
